data.title: Chiang Kai
data.meta_description: Turbocharge your history revision with our revolutionary new app! Clever Lili is here to help you ace your exams.
data.text:
Chiang Kai-shek was a Chinese , politician and general. He led the Guomindang (GMD), often referred to as the Chinese Nationalist Party, and was leader of the Republic of China until his defeat in the Chinese Civil War.

Chiang played 3 key roles during his life:

❖ He was one of the founding figures of the Chinese Nationalist Party (GMD).

❖ By the mid 1920s, he had consolidated power and became ruler of the Republic of China in 1928.

❖ He waged war on the CCP and Japan, before being defeated by the CCP in 1949. He fled China for Taiwan where he was until his death in 1975.
